<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,359,528]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,359,384]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[280,585,359,384]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Female and subadult male.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[592,666,359,384]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Telsidae" genus="Telson" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilostomatoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Telson</taxonomicName>
short, with 
<number box="[800,814,360,384]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.0">1</number>
pair lateral setae, 
<number box="[1018,1032,360,384]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.0">1</number>
pair stout terminal setae. 
<emphasis box="[199,320,396,421]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Adult male</emphasis>
. Antennule greatly expanded, with large brush of setae. Antenna short, not extending past posterior border of pleonite 
<number box="[358,375,431,456]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="5.0">5</number>
. Single pleopod with extremely stout peduncle, tiny rami with few long plumose setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,468,493]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Remarks.</emphasis>
No specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[520,842,468,493]" class="Malacostraca" family="Diastylidae" genus="Austroleptostylis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recalvastra">
<emphasis box="[520,842,468,493]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Austroleptostylis recalvastra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were seen in this study, the 
<collectingCountry box="[1164,1314,468,493]" name="New Zealand" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
records of this species are reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jones" box="[462,610,503,528]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Jones, N. S. (1963) The marine fauna of New Zealand: Crustaceans of the Order Cumacea. Memoirs of the New Zealand Oceanographic Institute, 23, 1 - 80." type="journal article" year="1963">
Jones (
<number box="[540,601,503,528]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1963.0">1963</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
